529
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:46,120
Please help me get the final confirmation soon, Hyungnim.

530
00:40:48,650 --> 00:40:50,620
Council Member.

531
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:56,980
CEO Seok takes good care of me already.

532
00:40:56,980 --> 00:41:00,150
No need for you to do this.

533
00:41:04,050 --> 00:41:08,590
You must be anxious since you own a lot of land around the golf course. Right?

534
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:13,170
No, it's just...

535
00:41:13,170 --> 00:41:14,930
Just? No way.

536
00:41:14,930 --> 00:41:18,370
You recently bought a lot of land under your wife's and kids' names.

537
00:41:18,370 --> 00:41:21,600
You'll make a fortune once the golf course is built.

538
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:27,090
But hey, haven't you always been a salaryman since being at Yoon Ho Seok's company?

539
00:41:27,090 --> 00:41:29,140
So, where did you get all that money?

540
00:41:29,140 --> 00:41:33,930
When Mr. Yoon is completely broke and even lost the foundation.

541
00:41:36,110 --> 00:41:39,110
That's why I'm so passionate about this.

542
00:41:39,110 --> 00:41:41,430
When I consider Father and Ji Won,

543
00:41:41,430 --> 00:41:44,600
I've made some good investments along the way.

544
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:46,490
For the sake of Mr. Yoon?

545
00:41:46,490 --> 00:41:50,290
There's nothing he hates more than the golf course.

546
00:41:51,030 --> 00:41:53,490
He doesn't get how the world works.

547
00:41:53,490 --> 00:41:56,740
You can't just chase ideals.

548
00:41:57,330 --> 00:41:59,400
Don't you think so?

549
00:42:00,020 --> 00:42:03,780
Anyway, please keep my land a secret.

550
00:42:03,780 --> 00:42:06,410
Look at you. You're shutting me up.

551
00:42:06,410 --> 00:42:08,500
Gosh...

552
00:42:10,840 --> 00:42:13,370
I'm just asking you for a favor.

553
00:42:13,930 --> 00:42:17,590
Father will be upset if he finds out.

554
00:42:18,340 --> 00:42:20,480
A dangerous fellow.

555
00:42:21,630 --> 00:42:23,370
Take this.

556
00:42:48,100 --> 00:42:52,800
   

557
00:42:57,850 --> 00:43:01,990
So, you took care of the parents who put up the banners?

558
00:43:01,990 --> 00:43:07,120
 Yes, I paid them off and handled it. But... 

559
00:43:07,910 --> 00:43:11,910
- Never mind. 
 - Say it. Why did you stop?

560
00:43:13,580 --> 00:43:17,660
Turns out it was Chairman Seok Ji Won who gathered the parents

561
00:43:17,660 --> 00:43:20,780
- regarding the driveway. 
  - What? 

562
00:43:20,780 --> 00:43:21,760
Ji Won?

563
00:43:21,760 --> 00:43:25,520
I suspect he wanted to impress my father.

564
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:26,670
What did he do?

565
00:43:26,670 --> 00:43:28,750
 I don't expect my father to do this, 

566
00:43:28,750 --> 00:43:31,240
but if Chairman Seok Ji Won becomes a part of that family,

567
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:35,500
my father will have a say in school or in golf course matters.

568
00:43:35,500 --> 00:43:36,960
I knew it.

569
00:43:36,960 --> 00:43:41,300
I thought it was suspicious that he had my son glued to his side.

570
00:43:41,300 --> 00:43:43,660
He's sitting back, knowing those two are seeing each other.

571
00:43:43,660 --> 00:43:46,170
Yes, he knows.

572
00:43:46,850 --> 00:43:51,440
So, what do you think about sending Chairman Seok Ji Won abroad again?

573
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:55,240
 Abroad? Send him to Dubai again? 

574
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:57,930
If the chairman is far away,

575
00:43:57,930 --> 00:44:00,460
it'll all sort itself out, won't it? 
    

576
00:44:00,460 --> 00:44:03,930
 It's true that nothing else will work on him. 

577
00:44:03,930 --> 00:44:05,970
That's what I'm saying.

578
00:44:15,210 --> 00:44:18,480
Let's hold hands so I cheer up.

579
00:44:19,340 --> 00:44:21,200
Out of the blue?

580
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:26,330
Yeah. I have to meet someone I really hate to see today.

581
00:44:26,970 --> 00:44:29,760
Then, don't meet him. Why are you meeting him?

582
00:44:29,760 --> 00:44:34,440
I want to prove that I'm not the Yoon Ji Won that he remembers.

583
00:44:35,460 --> 00:44:38,230
- You're meeting him at school, right? 
 - Yes, why?

584
00:44:38,230 --> 00:44:40,420
That way, I'm there.

585
00:44:40,420 --> 00:44:43,060
Gosh, of course, Chairman.

586
00:44:43,060 --> 00:44:46,070
Okay, have a good meeting. Be yourself.

587
00:44:46,070 --> 00:44:49,160
Always remember I'm by your side.

588
00:44:49,160 --> 00:44:50,900
Okay.

589
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:26,140
   

590
00:45:30,040 --> 00:45:32,530
 Wow, Yoon Ji Won. 

591
00:45:33,170 --> 00:45:34,960
 Hello? 

592
00:45:34,960 --> 00:45:36,970
I'm Yul's homeroom teacher, Yoon Ji Won.

593
00:45:36,970 --> 00:45:39,530
Can we meet today?

594
00:45:51,240 --> 00:45:52,800
Look.

595
00:45:52,800 --> 00:45:55,600
You don't even pretend to listen to me, Dad.

596
00:45:55,600 --> 00:45:59,610
I told you not to come back. I had to transfer all because of you.

597
00:45:59,610 --> 00:46:02,180
Do you want everyone here to find out my dad's a cheater?

598
00:46:02,180 --> 00:46:04,390
You got hurt.

599
00:46:04,390 --> 00:46:07,100
You're young, so you don't know. But in situations like this,

600
00:46:07,100 --> 00:46:09,800
- scolding the teacher... 
 - Cut the bullshit.

601
00:46:09,800 --> 00:46:12,100
I clearly said it was nothing.

602
00:46:12,100 --> 00:46:15,100
Just keep having affairs with young women, like you've been doing.

603
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:18,510
Hey, Jeong Yul. I told you that's not true. It's a misunderstanding.

604
00:46:18,510 --> 00:46:21,120
She's barely five years older than me.

605
00:46:21,120 --> 00:46:24,000
The girl Mom slapped.

606
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:25,810
- Disgusting. 
 - Disgusting?

607
00:46:25,810 --> 00:46:27,760
How dare you talk to your dad like that? Disgusting?

608
00:46:27,760 --> 00:46:30,930
I'm embarrassed that you're my dad and disgusted by you.

609
00:46:30,930 --> 00:46:32,290
You know that?

610
00:46:32,290 --> 00:46:33,710
Jeong Yul.

611
00:46:33,710 --> 00:46:34,980
Hey!

612
00:46:34,980 --> 00:46:37,600
How dare she... Hey, Jeong Yul!

613
00:46:46,500 --> 00:46:49,370
Whoa, Yoon Ji Won.

614
00:46:49,370 --> 00:46:51,380
Good to see you.

615
00:46:51,380 --> 00:46:53,280
Gosh...

616
00:46:54,530 --> 00:46:56,390
Hey.

617
00:46:57,300 --> 00:46:59,050
Ji Won,

618
00:46:59,050 --> 00:47:03,170
I was hurt that you ran off and ignored my calls. It's been so long.

619
00:47:03,170 --> 00:47:04,800
I'm sorry, Yul's father.

620
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:07,840
"Father"? Gosh, father...

621
00:47:07,840 --> 00:47:11,210
I feel tickled by you calling me that.

622
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:13,310
Will you keep talking down to me?

623
00:47:13,310 --> 00:47:15,330
It's just you and me. What's wrong with that?

624
00:47:15,330 --> 00:47:17,850
I'm just excited to see you.

625
00:47:23,100 --> 00:47:27,000
- You're not here for Yul, are you? 
 - No.

626
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:31,170
Of course, I'm here for my daughter, but we can talk about that later.

627
00:47:31,170 --> 00:47:33,690
Ji Won, how have you been?

628
00:47:33,690 --> 00:47:38,450
I've been curious how you've been doing. And a teacher... wow...

629
00:47:38,450 --> 00:47:41,540
I didn't think you could lead a professional life.

630
00:47:41,540 --> 00:47:43,880
I've been curious, too.

631
00:47:43,880 --> 00:47:46,300
What you're up to, CEO.

632
00:47:46,300 --> 00:47:49,250
- And? 
 - I wondered if you still rely on

633
00:47:49,250 --> 00:47:52,780
money and power to bully the weak,

634
00:47:52,780 --> 00:47:54,880
and I was right.

635
00:47:56,060 --> 00:47:57,520
How dare you? Hey...

636
00:47:57,520 --> 00:48:00,090
Sleeping around with girls your daughter's age

637
00:48:00,090 --> 00:48:02,740
and getting caught by your daughter.

638
00:48:02,740 --> 00:48:05,820
- I knew you'd live like this. 
 - "I knew you'd live like this"?

639
00:48:05,820 --> 00:48:07,720
- Yes. 
 - Yes? Hey!

640
00:48:07,720 --> 00:48:09,790
How dare a teacher treat a parent like this?

641
00:48:09,790 --> 00:48:12,100
With my kid's face all messed up? I won't let this slide.

642
00:48:12,100 --> 00:48:15,050
Bring the perpetrator here!

643
00:48:15,050 --> 00:48:18,570
If you'd like to raise an issue about this incident, please file a formal complaint

644
00:48:18,570 --> 00:48:20,640
to the school or the Office of Education, CEO.

645
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:22,760
Damn...

646
00:48:22,760 --> 00:48:26,470
This school is full of lunatics. You and the chairman.

647
00:48:26,470 --> 00:48:32,100
Please reconsider whether you'd be torturing me or torturing Yul

648
00:48:32,100 --> 00:48:34,750
by doing that, CEO.

649
00:48:34,750 --> 00:48:36,500
Hey.

650
00:48:37,780 --> 00:48:39,280
Aren't you scared of me?

651
00:48:39,280 --> 00:48:42,420
No. I'm not scared.

652
00:48:43,010 --> 00:48:46,120
You're nothing to me now.

653
00:48:47,900 --> 00:48:49,910
Okay, then.

654
00:48:52,820 --> 00:48:54,710
Hey.

655
00:48:57,250 --> 00:49:00,060
Hey. You say your piece, and that's it?

656
00:49:00,060 --> 00:49:01,600
You're not scared of me?

657
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,740
You're a teacher, and I'm a parent.

658
00:49:03,740 --> 00:49:06,220
Do you have a brain?

659
00:49:07,100 --> 00:49:08,520
Look at this.

660
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:10,720
How dare you...

661
00:49:10,720 --> 00:49:14,200
Hey, what is this? Hey!

662
00:49:18,660 --> 00:49:20,440
Hey...

663
00:49:20,440 --> 00:49:22,030
What is this, you bastard?

664
00:49:22,030 --> 00:49:23,460
You punched me?

665
00:49:23,460 --> 00:49:25,270
Get out if you don't want to get punched again.

666
00:49:25,270 --> 00:49:29,400
Hey! You think I'll let this slide?

667
00:49:36,940 --> 00:49:38,710
Shit!

668
00:49:38,710 --> 00:49:44,070
If you make an issue out of this, I'll respond with the utmost care.

669
00:49:44,730 --> 00:49:47,460
Get home safely.

670
00:49:47,460 --> 00:49:50,360
You bastard...

671
00:50:00,430 --> 00:50:02,580
Damn it.

672
00:50:06,840 --> 00:50:08,240
Are you okay, sir?

673
00:50:08,240 --> 00:50:11,880
You should've been careful.

674
00:50:11,880 --> 00:50:13,410
- I'm sorry! 
 - What is this?

675
00:50:13,410 --> 00:50:14,910
- Are you okay? 
 - That must hurt.

676
00:50:14,910 --> 00:50:16,870
- Who are you? 
 - Are you okay?

677
00:50:16,870 --> 00:50:18,980
Let go!

678
00:50:18,980 --> 00:50:21,430
I'm sorry.

679
00:50:26,740 --> 00:50:29,930
Geez, what shall we do?

680
00:50:29,930 --> 00:50:32,320
Gosh...

681
00:50:36,560 --> 00:50:39,100
The school nurse happens to be gone.

682
00:50:39,100 --> 00:50:41,110
Ouch!

683
00:50:41,110 --> 00:50:42,980
Stay still.

684
00:50:42,980 --> 00:50:45,740
What if he actually makes a big deal out of this?

685
00:50:45,740 --> 00:50:48,110
What else? I'll also make a big deal out of it.

686
00:50:48,110 --> 00:50:51,400
Don't worry. Bastards like that stomp on those who look weaker

687
00:50:51,400 --> 00:50:54,930
but are useless, otherwise. He has too much to lose.

688
00:50:54,930 --> 00:50:57,340
Ouch, it stings!

689
00:50:57,340 --> 00:50:58,560
What a crybaby.

690
00:50:58,560 --> 00:51:01,970
I'm not! I'm bleeding a lot, and it stings.

691
00:51:01,970 --> 00:51:05,460
- Where do you think you're raising your voice? 
 - At the school health office!

692
00:51:05,460 --> 00:51:10,380
So much time has passed, yet we say the same stuff we used to say.

693
00:51:12,270 --> 00:51:15,150
Seok Ji Won, you used to be so cute back then.

694
00:51:15,150 --> 00:51:19,780
What are you talking about? I'm cuter now.

695
00:51:24,450 --> 00:51:26,220
Cute.

696
00:51:26,220 --> 00:51:29,100
So cute. Cute!

697
00:51:29,710 --> 00:51:32,440
- Ouch... 
 - Don't press it just because it stings!

698
00:51:32,440 --> 00:51:34,450
Blow on it.

699
00:51:40,780 --> 00:51:43,360
You must've been shocked the other day.

700
00:51:44,970 --> 00:51:46,610
Yes...

701
00:51:46,610 --> 00:51:51,940
I was so shocked that my heart was in my throat.

702
00:51:53,020 --> 00:51:54,770
I'm sorry.

703
00:51:55,930 --> 00:51:58,000
A long time ago,

704
00:52:00,000 --> 00:52:02,370
not knowing what happened,

705
00:52:03,260 --> 00:52:06,330
I just thought I was dumped.

706
00:52:06,990 --> 00:52:10,690
But I found out she left me...

707
00:52:11,570 --> 00:52:13,980
and raised Hye Soo by herself.

708
00:52:13,980 --> 00:52:18,570
And I found that out too late.

709
00:52:24,860 --> 00:52:30,920
There are moments in life when you wish you had known things sooner.

710
00:52:31,930 --> 00:52:38,540
But the less time you spend regretting the past, the better.

711
00:52:39,470 --> 00:52:42,170
Thank you, Miss Maeng.

712
00:52:43,780 --> 00:52:46,860
How about a drink— no...

713
00:52:46,860 --> 00:52:50,520
A meal. Buy me a meal, then.

714
00:53:08,310 --> 00:53:09,700
What?

715
00:53:09,700 --> 00:53:12,130
You still feel suspicious?

716
00:53:12,130 --> 00:53:13,940
I'm not interested.

717
00:53:13,940 --> 00:53:18,440
My dad wants to make a big deal out of our fight.

718
00:53:18,440 --> 00:53:20,110
Just say it was nothing.

719
00:53:20,110 --> 00:53:22,300
Your dad?

720
00:53:22,300 --> 00:53:24,790
Biologically, yes.

721
00:53:26,850 --> 00:53:28,970
You have a problem dad, too...

722
00:53:28,970 --> 00:53:30,870
"Too"?

723
00:53:38,750 --> 00:53:40,830
Go Hye Soo, is the nurse your dad—

724
00:53:40,830 --> 00:53:45,220
Start a rumor if you want. I don't care.

725
00:53:53,130 --> 00:53:55,600
You were there, too?

726
00:53:57,130 --> 00:53:59,730
That's the day Go Hye Soo fainted with a nosebleed while studying.

727
00:53:59,730 --> 00:54:02,200
Eom Gi Seok and I carried her to the school health office.

728
00:54:02,200 --> 00:54:04,500
The school nurse took her home.

729
00:54:04,500 --> 00:54:06,740
Eom Gi Seok and I got in outside the school gates.

730
00:54:06,740 --> 00:54:09,640
No clue who took the photo, leaving us out completely.

731
00:54:09,640 --> 00:54:13,140
You're friends with Go Hye Soo. Who's to say you aren't covering for her?

732
00:54:13,140 --> 00:54:16,480
- Hey. 
 - I was there, too.

733
00:54:17,130 --> 00:54:18,880
The day she had a nosebleed.

734
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:21,670
I was in the classroom. That's the day you're talking about, right?

735
00:54:21,670 --> 00:54:23,440
Right.

736
00:54:23,440 --> 00:54:26,980
You saw and ignored us that day. Right?

737
00:54:28,490 --> 00:54:30,960
You believe Jeong Yul even though she fought with Go Hye Soo?

738
00:54:30,960 --> 00:54:33,360
Yeah. Our class president wouldn't do that.

739
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:34,860
And the school nurse, either.

740
00:54:34,860 --> 00:54:37,070
And he's denying it, too.

741
00:54:37,070 --> 00:54:39,560
Even Go Hye Soo's mom moved on.

742
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:43,000
Why are you still stuck on it? So weird.

743
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:47,870
I'm just saying you guys are friends with the class president. Nothing more.

744
00:55:22,390 --> 00:55:24,400
Where are we going?

745
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:27,190
It's no fun if I tell you.

746
00:55:27,190 --> 00:55:29,670
- Not the playground? 
 - Playground?

747
00:55:29,670 --> 00:55:31,800
We'll go there next time.

748
00:55:31,800 --> 00:55:35,390
You look like you prepared tons, and you can't wait to show me.

749
00:55:35,390 --> 00:55:37,220
What could it be?

750
00:55:37,220 --> 00:55:38,500
Is it a special day?

751
00:55:38,500 --> 00:55:41,140
I didn't prepare anything. It's nothing like that.

752
00:55:41,140 --> 00:55:43,980
I just want to have a casual meal.

753
00:55:43,980 --> 00:55:47,300
Really? You didn't prepare anything?

754
00:55:47,300 --> 00:55:49,990
Nothing's there.

755
00:55:58,850 --> 00:56:00,830
What's wrong?

756
00:56:00,830 --> 00:56:02,170
It's not here.

757
00:56:02,170 --> 00:56:05,340
It's not here. Nothing...

758
00:56:20,250 --> 00:56:22,390
- Your grandpa's not home right now, right? 
 - Yeah.

759
00:56:22,390 --> 00:56:25,590
He just left the house to meet with the town elders.

760
00:56:25,590 --> 00:56:28,090
How could I make a mistake like this?

761
00:56:33,640 --> 00:56:34,880
What did you leave behind?

762
00:56:34,880 --> 00:56:37,600
Let me go fetch it quickly.

763
00:56:59,340 --> 00:57:01,050
Did you find it? Your secret?

764
00:57:01,050 --> 00:57:04,520
There's no secret. Get up. We better rush out.

765
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:06,220
Wait a second. Let me grab some water.

766
00:57:06,220 --> 00:57:09,700
No. Drink when we get there.

767
00:57:13,550 --> 00:57:15,460
Grandpa!

768
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:25,580
- Grandpa. 
 - Hey.

769
00:57:25,580 --> 00:57:27,020
Your dinner plans are already over?

770
00:57:27,020 --> 00:57:29,310
No, no. I left something behind.

771
00:57:29,310 --> 00:57:32,920
Gosh, I keep forgetting stuff. Let's see...

772
00:57:32,920 --> 00:57:34,800
Where...

773
00:57:34,800 --> 00:57:38,780
- I think I left it on the second floor... 
 - What? Second floor?

774
00:57:38,780 --> 00:57:41,020
What's wrong? Why are you screaming?

775
00:57:41,020 --> 00:57:42,800
- I'll go... 
 - No, no.

776
00:57:42,800 --> 00:57:45,470
What's wrong? It's okay.

777
00:57:45,470 --> 00:57:49,230
Oh, you left something on the second floor...

778
00:57:56,100 --> 00:57:57,790
Here it is.

779
00:57:57,790 --> 00:57:59,410
Fishing poles?

780
00:58:01,230 --> 00:58:04,900
I was giving it to Mr. Kim since I don't use it.

781
00:58:04,900 --> 00:58:10,020
But I kept forgetting about it, and the season's over now.

782
00:58:12,190 --> 00:58:13,770
Oh, right.

783
00:58:14,340 --> 00:58:17,890
Didn't you say you have plans, too?

784
00:58:17,890 --> 00:58:19,410
Me?

785
00:58:19,410 --> 00:58:22,410
I should go, too. I had some spare time.

786
00:58:22,410 --> 00:58:24,450
I'll get going soon.

787
00:58:45,110 --> 00:58:48,400
- Grandpa wants you to come out this instant. 
 - What?

788
00:58:48,400 --> 00:58:50,430
